# Environment Variables Example for ASE Tag Software Frontend
# 
# Copy this file to create your environment-specific configurations:
# - .env.development (for local development) - auto-loaded with 'npm run dev'
# - .env.production (for production builds) - auto-loaded with 'npm run build'

# =============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT CONFIGURATION (.env.development)
# =============================================================================
# Backend API URL for development (local server)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api

# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION CONFIGURATION (.env.production)
# =============================================================================
# Backend API URL for production (deployed server)
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.com/api

# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# =============================================================================
# - Vite automatically loads .env.development in dev mode (npm run dev)
# - Vite automatically loads .env.production in build mode (npm run build)
# - All frontend environment variables MUST start with VITE_ prefix
# - Always include /api at the end of backend URLs
# - Do NOT commit actual .env files to version control
